node.text:
The ripple effect of our Water Positive approach is far reaching:

💧Installing drip irrigation with partners 
💧Reforesting depleted areas 
💧Restoring wetlands 
💧Enlarging riverbeds 

Visit the link in our bio to discover how our water business is leading the regeneration of water ⬆️ 

#Water #Regeneration #Nestlé

Let's take action to stop the suffering of Herta pigs and all animals exploited on behalf of Nestlé!
Schocking practices in a French farm of the Herta brand were made public at the end of 2020 by the association L214. Questioned by the Coalition for animal rights (COA) and Animae, two Swiss associations, Nestlé has still not acknowledged and denounced the abuse of pigs in the farm.
Yet Nestlé owned 100% of the Herta brand from 1986 to the end of 2019, i.e. for more than 30 years. This brand practices a form of intensive farming that is prohibited in Switzerland. Currently, Nestlé still has a 40% share in Herta
So what are you guys doing about your current cease and desist in California.

@essentiallypure Thanks for reaching out. We no longer have any spring water operations in the US, including California. You can let Blue Triton Brands know any feedback. If you’d like to learn more about our global water stewardship, check out: https://bit.ly/2SIr5wM
How’s your African child slave labor going @nestle ???
Stealing water rights from third world countries and using slave labor
Nestle is still financing Belarusian state TV that broadcasts fakes and interviews tortured people against their willing. The company does not care about you nor their reputation💩🍫
Nothing you’re doing is gonna equal the damage you’ve done, not even 1%
Cool now set your child slaves free

@thatgogodude Hi, child exploitation is simply unacceptable and goes against everything we stand for. We work with our suppliers and local communities to prevent & address child labor risks in our supply chain. We want to be able to trace all our cocoa back to a specific group of farms and ensure 100% of the cocoa we use is sourced within our special program. Please follow our progress here: https://nes.tl/AskChildLabor
